			<div class="content" id="post-content-2057441">
									

<p>Wikibooks says 'salut' is informal:</p>
<p><a href="http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/French/Lessons/Greetings">http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/French/Lessons/Greetings</a></p>
<p>As far as I can tell, 'Salutations' means roughly the same in French as it does in English: &quot;salutations distinguées&quot;, for example, means &quot;best regards&quot;. It is of course possible&#8230; probable, even, that the phrase is a butchery of the French language.</p>
<p>If anyone asks, I did it on purpose. As&#8230; uh&#8230; an artistic choice? Yes.</p>

